{"id":448026,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Glawogger","text":"Michael Glawogger (3 December 1959 \u2013 23 April 2014) was an Austrian movie director, screenwriter, cinematographer and actor. His best known movies were \"Megacities\" (1998), \"Workingman's Death\" (2005) and \"Whores' Glory\" (2011). He was born in Graz.\nGlawogger died from malaria on 23 April 2014 during a movie production in Liberia. He was 54.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Austrians","surface_form":"Austrian","offset":59},{"uri":"Movie_director","surface_form":"movie director","offset":68},{"uri":"Screenwriter","surface_form":"screenwriter","offset":84},{"uri":"Cinematographer","surface_form":"cinematographer","offset":98},{"uri":"Actor","surface_form":"actor","offset":118},{"uri":"Movie","surface_form":"movie","offset":140},{"uri":"Megacities_(movie)","surface_form":"Megacities","offset":153},{"uri":"Workingman%27s_Death","surface_form":"Workingman's Death","offset":174},{"uri":"Whores%27_Glory","surface_form":"Whores' Glory","offset":206},{"uri":"Graz","surface_form":"Graz","offset":244},{"uri":"Malaria","surface_form":"malaria","offset":270},{"uri":"Liberia","surface_form":"Liberia","offset":324}]}